summary:
Here is a summarized version of the Security Council document:

The Security Council,

Noting the International Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia's ("the International Tribunal") letter and the Secretary-General's letter, 

Recalling its previous resolutions, including 827 (1993), 1503 (2003), 1534 (2004), and 1877 (2009),

Noting the International Tribunal's assessment that it will not complete all its work in 2010,

Decides to:

1. Extend the terms of office of trial judges until 30 June 2010 and appeals judges until 31 December 2012, or until completion of their cases;
2. Allow Judges Kimberley Prost and Ole Bjørn Støle to complete the Popović case;
3. Temporarily increase the number of ad litem judges to 13, returning to 12 by 31 March 2010;
4. Allow ad litem Judges Prost and Støle to serve beyond the cumulative period provided for under the Statute;

Requests the President of the International Tribunal to submit an updated trial and appeals schedule.

Decides to remain seized of the matter.
